{"type":"message-part","messageId":"c6360d5e-dcc4-4507-9b96-bf83717aa675","role":"user","index":0,"part":{"type":"text","text":"# Preserving your work\n\nSave a copy of files you create during this task to `/logs/artifacts/`. This directory is preserved after the run so outputs can be inspected. Organize with subdirectories if helpful (e.g., `/logs/artifacts/code/`, `/logs/artifacts/reports/`). The directory already exists and is writable.\n\n---\n\n# TypeScript Windmill Script Returning a Structured Object\n\n## Background\n\nWindmill scripts can return structured objects, not just primitives. The returned object is serialized to JSON and made available to downstream flow steps or displayed in the Windmill UI. This is useful for scripts that produce multiple named output values.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Create a TypeScript script at `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/user_info.ts`.\n- The script must export an async `main` function with this signature:\n  ```typescript\n  export async function main(id: number, name: string, active: boolean = true)\n  ```\n- The function must return an object with exactly these fields:\n  ```typescript\n  { id: number, name: string, active: boolean, display: string }\n  ```\n  Where `display` is the string `` `[${id}] ${name} (${active ? 'active' : 'inactive'})` ``.\n- Create the metadata file at `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/user_info.script.yaml` with:\n  - `summary: \"Build a user info object\"`\n  - `language: typescript`\n\n## Implementation Guide\n\n1. Create `f/scripts/user_info.ts`:\n   ```typescript\n   export async function main(id: number, name: string, active: boolean = true) {\n     return {\n       id,\n       name,\n       active,\n       display: `[${id}] ${name} (${active ? 'active' : 'inactive'})`,\n     };\n   }\n   ```\n2. Create `f/scripts/user_info.script.yaml`:\n   ```yaml\n   summary: \"Build a user info object\"\n   language: typescript\n   ```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Project path: `/home/user/windmill-project`\n- Script path: `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/user_info.ts`\n- Metadata path: `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/user_info.script.yaml`\n- The `display` field format must be: `[${id}] ${name} (active)` or `[${id}] ${name} (inactive)`\n\n## Integrations\n\nNone."}}
